From 461fdbddc114303cffa8aacdd1f8bbeeb6c779c7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Tue, 17 Mar 2026 15:07:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 025/174] PGCL: fix ELF_EXEC_PAGESIZE across all architectures

ELF_EXEC_PAGESIZE was still PAGE_SIZE on riscv, arm64, loongarch,
mips, powerpc, s390, and sparc64. With PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4
(PAGE_SIZE=64KB), ELF segments with 4KB-aligned p_vaddr get rounded
to 64KB boundaries by ELF_PAGESTART/ELF_PAGEALIGN, causing text and
data segments that are < 64KB apart to map at the same address. The
data segment's mmap then overwrites the text mapping, and the first
instruction fetch hits an instruction page fault (signal 11).

Verified: riscv64 init was crashing with cause=12 (instruction page
fault) at entry point 0x10912 because the data segment at 0x11000
mapped over the text segment at 0x10000 when both rounded down to
the same 64KB boundary.

Fix: change ELF_EXEC_PAGESIZE to MMUPAGE_SIZE on all architectures,
matching the x86 fix already in place.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
